First of all, will miss all you folks from karana- best of luck on your new server, but consider coming back &quot;home&quot; okay? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Second, for all the bashing it takes, the KGC rotation DID work pretty well.  Very few if any gods or named mobs ever went unkilled, and the planes were cleared regularly and fairly completely (tho not &quot;farmed&quot; as I've heard they are elsewhere).  What did this do?  It GREATLY spread out the distribution of the uber gear.  Instead of a few large guilds having everybody AND their twinks in full planar, ALL the planes-capable guilds (and many non-guilded guests) got a shot at the nice stuff.<br>
<br>
Was it always good?  No, of course not.  Despite rumors to the contrary, the &quot;big guilds&quot; like Grey Hawke (which I'm in) and a few of the European ones actually got far LESS opportunity than we would have under a FFA system.  We had/have more than enough people to camp/kill all the pre-velious named spawns at will, but instead SHARE them in a rotation.  It is a non-optimal but equitable solution to a tough situation... /rude verant for putting in such long spawn times on the &quot;good&quot; mobs. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Anyway, I do hope things work out for yall; I really think that FFA is a bad idea, but will be watching to see how it turns out.  Good luck!<br>
<br>
RdT.<br>
a.k.a.<br>
Remf da Troll<br>
